<TITLE> Violence erupts over BCL leader's arrest in Brahmanbarhia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbarhia, July 3 (bdnews24.com)Violence erupted in Brahmanbarhia town after police on Friday arrested district Chhatra League president Mahmudul Haque Bhuiyan at his residence in Kaziparha. Rezaul Karim Bhuiyan, Brahmanbarhia Sadar police chief, said they arrested Mahmud at 3am on charges of tender manipulation and abduction filed with the police. As the news of Mahmud's arrest spread, the district BCL activists brought out processions at around 11am protesting the arrest and demanding his immediate release. They vandalised public property and carried arson attacks on TA Road. The whole town turned into a veritable battle theatre. The angry activists clashed with police, leaving at least 10 people including a police constable, injured. Seriously injured constable Habibur Rahman, 28, was admitted to Brahmanbarhia Sadar Hospital. The Sadar spuerintendent of police was also mauled as he tried to defuse the scuffles. Police reinforcements later brought the situation under control. Demonstrators also halted traffic movement at Bhadughar on the Comilla-Sylhet highway. The Brahmanbarhia Sadar police chief said police reached the Comilla-Sylhet highway at 3:45pm, dispersed the BCL activists blocking it and cleared it for the traffic. bdnews24.com correspondent said at 4:30pm that the activists were parading the town streets and there was widespread tension all around. bdn
